[recv] {"method":"item/completed","params":{"item":{"type":"agentMessage","id":"msg_0f01ee88f34974250169cac5e21c288191a0a2eabe0a1be78b","text":"Built the breakout in [index.circuit.tsx](/workspace/index.circuit.tsx). It uses JLC-imported `RP2040`, `ME6211C33M5G_N`, `HX_USB3_1TYPE_C_16P_FS`, and `YLED0603R`, plus local flash/crystal wrappers so the board stays off the tscircuit registry and does not use `routingDisabled`. The board exposes two 20-pin headers, USB-C power/data, 3.3 V regulation, QSPI flash, 12 MHz crystal, and a GPIO25 LED.\n\nValidation:\n- `npm run typecheck` passed.\n- `tsci check netlist /workspace/index.circuit.tsx` passed with 0 errors / 0 warnings.\n- `tsci check placement /workspace/index.circuit.tsx` passed after rotating/fixing the headers and moving a few support parts.\n- `tsci build /workspace/index.circuit.tsx` regenerated [circuit.json](/workspace/dist/index/circuit.json), but the CLI did not exit cleanly within the wait window after writing the file.\n\n**TSCircuit Developer Feedback**\n- What was confusing or surprising in the tscircuit workflow: `pinheader` defaulted to a horizontal PCB orientation, which made the headers hang off-board until I explicitly rotated them; that was not obvious from the props alone.\n- What wasted the most time: JLC search/import coverage was inconsistent for obvious RP2040 support parts like flash and crystal, so I had to fall back to local wrappers after several searches.\n- What docs, APIs, or tooling changes would have helped: clearer examples for `pinheader` PCB orientation, a documented “raw JLC part with user pin labels” pattern, and better guidance on when `build` is still routing versus effectively done.\n- Any specific friction points encountered during this run: JSX arrays of `<trace />` triggered a React `key` warning that was harmless for netlisting but noisy and misleading; `tsci build` wrote `dist/index/circuit.json` but appeared to keep running without a clear completion signal.","phase":"final_answer","memoryCitation":null},"threadId":"019d400b-330e-7811-ade7-7ed8affa8eb0","turnId":"019d400b-3310-7cc1-9f25-f30a1c470533"}}
